00:42:45.030 --> 00:42:47.520
you now have a business brand.

00:42:47.520 --> 00:42:50.380
You have this cultural
brand as well.

00:42:50.380 --> 00:42:51.900
And you also now,
I'm hearing, you

00:42:51.900 --> 00:42:53.970
have this other thing
that's mommyhood

00:42:53.970 --> 00:42:57.990
that might prevent either the
evolution of or the building

00:42:57.990 --> 00:42:59.940
or separation of another brand.

00:42:59.940 --> 00:43:01.710
What does your
brand mean to you,

00:43:01.710 --> 00:43:05.020
and can you share your
thoughts of that over time?

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:07.350
ANI DIFRANCO: Yeah, sure.

00:43:07.350 --> 00:43:09.390
Let me see.

00:43:09.390 --> 00:43:14.356
I think what I tend to
do is not think about it.

00:43:19.738 --> 00:43:25.240
When you were talking of all
the elements in your question,

00:43:25.240 --> 00:43:29.130
I was thinking about a story.

00:43:29.130 --> 00:43:31.590
I hear so many wonderful
stories from people

00:43:31.590 --> 00:43:34.770
who have intersected my
music or my brand even.

00:43:37.290 --> 00:43:42.050
I heard a story and
I get these letters

00:43:42.050 --> 00:43:47.310
that are just like food for
me that nourish me back.

00:43:47.310 --> 00:43:49.620
And I got a letter
a little while ago

00:43:49.620 --> 00:43:54.690
from a mom who is
a fan of my work.

00:43:54.690 --> 00:43:58.770
And she had a Righteous Babe
sweatshirt with the logo.

00:44:03.190 --> 00:44:05.410
And her young
daughter said to her,

00:44:05.410 --> 00:44:09.400
"Mommy, is that a girl or a
boy," striking this muscle man

00:44:09.400 --> 00:44:13.400
pose but with a skirt,
the little logo.

00:44:13.400 --> 00:44:16.540
That started off as a
picture of me hamming it up.

00:44:16.540 --> 00:44:19.270
I hate cameras so I'm going
to do something ridiculous.

00:44:19.270 --> 00:44:21.190
And then that became
the logo and that

00:44:21.190 --> 00:44:24.025
became the brand,
Righteous Babe.

00:44:26.690 --> 00:44:28.370
So here's a little
girl who I don't

00:44:28.370 --> 00:44:32.660
know talking to her mom who's
found something in my music.

00:44:32.660 --> 00:44:34.150
"Mommy, is that
a girl or a boy?"

00:44:34.150 --> 00:44:36.170
"That's a girl sweetie."

00:44:36.170 --> 00:44:42.340
And then the little girl said,
"Is she so, so, so, so strong?"

00:44:42.340 --> 00:44:47.240
And her mom said, "Yeah,
she's so, so, so, so strong."

00:44:47.240 --> 00:44:48.490
And this is all in the letter.

00:44:48.490 --> 00:44:51.100
And then she said
there was a pause

00:44:51.100 --> 00:44:55.760
and her five-year-old said,
"I want to be like that."

00:44:55.760 --> 00:44:57.205
And I thought, whoa, a logo.

00:45:00.842 --> 00:45:02.300
And I don't think
that that's going

00:45:02.300 --> 00:45:05.390
to inspire me to think about
it or how can I tweak the logo

00:45:05.390 --> 00:45:10.670
or how can we work the brand
to make more value for--

00:45:10.670 --> 00:45:15.270
I just try to do what
I do and be who I am

00:45:15.270 --> 00:45:18.330
and write the best song
I can be and give it

00:45:18.330 --> 00:45:21.420
in the most honest way
I can in whatever moment

00:45:21.420 --> 00:45:27.030
and hope that these peripheral
things, like the idea

00:45:27.030 --> 00:45:31.290
of Righteous Babe Records
and the look of that logo,

00:45:31.290 --> 00:45:34.110
will do their own
work around that.

00:45:34.110 --> 00:45:38.640
If I just stay focused on what
I know and what I'm good at,

00:45:38.640 --> 00:45:42.720
that those peripheral things
like the Righteous Babe Brand--

00:45:42.720 --> 00:45:45.870
I mean, we are trying to
put a festival together.

00:45:45.870 --> 00:45:49.380
And maybe I have been
inspired by my new team

00:45:49.380 --> 00:45:54.910
to contemplate it more, to try
to reinvent Righteous Babe.

00:45:54.910 --> 00:45:58.750
And what does it mean to stand
at the intersection of art

00:45:58.750 --> 00:46:02.590
and politics and who else
can we help or invite

00:46:02.590 --> 00:46:05.380
in or what other
communities can we

00:46:05.380 --> 00:46:08.960
help to bring closer
together, to make

00:46:08.960 --> 00:46:13.360
stronger through a festival,
through a branded festival?

00:46:13.360 --> 00:46:17.650
So I try to work with people
who do understand such things

00:46:17.650 --> 00:46:20.860
and can build
momentum around them.

00:46:20.860 --> 00:46:28.204
But for me, I just try to focus
