00:46:53.600 --> 00:46:54.770
deserves it.

00:46:54.770 --> 00:46:56.480
And I wonder if
that functionality

00:46:56.480 --> 00:46:59.300
speaks to what you were
saying as far as not having

00:46:59.300 --> 00:47:01.430
to worry about
developing the brand,

00:47:01.430 --> 00:47:04.010
just doing what
needs to get done?

00:47:04.010 --> 00:47:08.180
ANI DIFRANCO: Yeah, one of the
great ironies of my existence,

00:47:08.180 --> 00:47:11.450
if you're me, is this
label entrepreneur

00:47:11.450 --> 00:47:15.390
that has followed my
name for 30 years.

00:47:15.390 --> 00:47:19.280
And it's so not the point.

00:47:19.280 --> 00:47:23.740
It's like so far from
the point that it

00:47:23.740 --> 00:47:25.630
used to really bother me.

00:47:25.630 --> 00:47:28.840
I mean of all the things that--

00:47:28.840 --> 00:47:34.380
songwriter, activist,
entrepreneur?

00:47:34.380 --> 00:47:38.290
OK, right, I guess I
started a record company.

00:47:38.290 --> 00:47:43.030
But the whole point was really
to avoid the music business.

00:47:43.030 --> 00:47:47.230
The whole point was can you
just make music your job

00:47:47.230 --> 00:47:55.520
without having to get in
bed with business people,

00:47:55.520 --> 00:48:00.110
bottom line-oriented people?

00:48:00.110 --> 00:48:02.970
Not that the music industry
is full of bad people.

00:48:02.970 --> 00:48:04.425
They're good people.

00:48:07.790 --> 00:48:10.100
I think I was such
an idealistic kid

00:48:10.100 --> 00:48:15.050
that it's sort of I looked at
the intersection of business

00:48:15.050 --> 00:48:19.520
and corporate culture and art
and I see commodification.

00:48:19.520 --> 00:48:21.980
I see everything
beautiful and vital

00:48:21.980 --> 00:48:25.670
come out of the underground
get commodified and die.

00:48:25.670 --> 00:48:27.920
And I thought, [GROANS].

00:48:27.920 --> 00:48:30.170
I don't want to be a
part of that process

00:48:30.170 --> 00:48:32.990
even if it serves me.

00:48:32.990 --> 00:48:36.690
I find that to be such a bummer.

00:48:36.690 --> 00:48:39.260
How else could it be done?

00:48:39.260 --> 00:48:44.390
So the point was
really just to never--

00:48:44.390 --> 00:48:48.080
I mean for me to just follow
my teachers, the people that

00:48:48.080 --> 00:48:55.060
really made my world bigger and
less about myself instead of,

00:48:55.060 --> 00:48:58.420
you should wear this and play
this song and make this happen

00:48:58.420 --> 00:48:59.920
and here's how to--

00:48:59.920 --> 00:49:03.140
it's just like, I don't
want to think about that.

00:49:03.140 --> 00:49:06.560
I want to think about
something meaningful.

00:49:06.560 --> 00:49:12.490
So yeah, I guess it was a
problem-solving process.

00:49:12.490 --> 00:49:14.440
It was never about
running a record company

00:49:14.440 --> 00:49:19.720
but about, how can I
dedicated as little energy

00:49:19.720 --> 00:49:21.339
in that direction as possible?

