you feel like you're
sort of inevitably

00:49:45.854 --> 00:49:49.120
in an embrace with Spotify,
Pandora, Apple Music, Google

00:49:49.120 --> 00:49:50.800
Play Music, whoever?

00:49:50.800 --> 00:49:53.860
And if you were a young
artist starting out right now,

00:49:53.860 --> 00:49:56.663
would you try to leverage those
or would you still try and do

00:49:56.663 --> 00:49:57.704
the whole thing yourself?

00:50:01.880 --> 00:50:06.710
ANI DIFRANCO: I mean, there's
so much to know and navigate now

00:50:06.710 --> 00:50:09.330
to have a career in music.

00:50:09.330 --> 00:50:13.790
And I certainly don't think I'm
a voice of authority or knowing

00:50:13.790 --> 00:50:15.650
necessarily.

00:50:15.650 --> 00:50:23.480
My basic approach is to
just let go, to just let go.

00:50:23.480 --> 00:50:30.140
As the music business and
the world changed around me,

00:50:30.140 --> 00:50:31.760
let go of the old.

00:50:31.760 --> 00:50:38.370
And is music free now and can
musicians have a job of music

00:50:38.370 --> 00:50:42.890
if it's just free and you
can't commodify it at all?

00:50:42.890 --> 00:50:46.310
And the little guy is
struggling so much.

00:50:46.310 --> 00:50:50.390
And people have asked me what
I make about these streaming

00:50:50.390 --> 00:50:52.540
and these--

00:50:52.540 --> 00:50:56.860
And for me, I just
have this sort

00:50:56.860 --> 00:51:05.150
of really basic primal
approach which is acceptance.

00:51:05.150 --> 00:51:08.520
I can't control how
people get their music.

00:51:12.220 --> 00:51:15.860
I just let it all happen.

00:51:15.860 --> 00:51:19.060
And I hope that the--

00:51:19.060 --> 00:51:23.630
and I have found through
this just sort of ignorant

00:51:23.630 --> 00:51:26.900
but faithful approach
of, I'm going

00:51:26.900 --> 00:51:32.600
to apply as much consciousness
as I can through my work

00:51:32.600 --> 00:51:37.220
and hope that that comes
back at me from the universe,

00:51:37.220 --> 00:51:43.550
hope that the universe has
a place for me in my art.

00:51:43.550 --> 00:51:45.740
It has found a place for me.

00:51:45.740 --> 00:51:47.390
So I'm one of the lucky ones.

00:51:47.390 --> 00:51:50.960
Maybe it's easy for me to
speak in such trite terms

00:51:50.960 --> 00:51:54.455
because the universe has
held me and I'm very lucky.

00:51:57.240 --> 00:52:00.720
But I think that when you are
in the groove, when you're

00:52:00.720 --> 00:52:04.890
in the flow of yourself,
of whoever you are

00:52:04.890 --> 00:52:07.920
and whatever you have
to offer, there is

00:52:07.920 --> 00:52:10.290
a place in the universe for it.

00:52:10.290 --> 00:52:17.700
So to calculate, [GRUNTS],,
what obstacles change the flow

00:52:17.700 --> 00:52:22.030
or guide it, I don't
worry about that.

00:52:22.030 --> 00:52:24.390
I just worry, am I
being true to myself?

00:52:24.390 --> 00:52:27.000
Am I giving what I have to give?

00:52:27.000 --> 00:52:34.850
Am I listening to the
voices that guide me?

00:52:34.850 --> 00:52:37.670
And so far it's worked out.

00:52:37.670 --> 00:52:41.884
[LAUGHS] I don't know if
that's an answer, but--

00:52:41.884 --> 00:52:42.550
AUDIENCE: It is.

